    <he>Galyleo Visualization Platform FAQ</he>

    <h3>Overview</h3>
    <p><strong>What is the Galyleo Visualization Platform?</strong></p>
    <p>The Galyleo Visualization Platform is a tool that allows users to design web-publishable dashboards with a simple drag-and-drop interface. Dashboards can be published to the web with a single click, making it easy to share insights and visualizations.</p>

    <p><strong>What makes Galyleo dashboards unique?</strong></p>
    <p>Dashboards created with Galyleo are pure HTML/JavaScript pages that can be served from any standard web server. This means they are lightweight, flexible, and secure, leveraging all standard web security mechanisms.</p>

    <h3>Features</h3>
    <p><strong>What charting libraries are supported?</strong></p>
    <p>Currently, Galyleo supports Google Charts. In the future, the platform will include support for all major open-source charting and mapping libraries, expanding its visualization capabilities.</p>

    <p><strong>How is the Galyleo Visualization Platform integrated with the Data Plane?</strong></p>
    <p>The platform is fully integrated with the Data Plane, allowing users to seamlessly include any Data Plane data source in their dashboards. This integration ensures easy access to real-time and static data for visualization.</p>

    <h3>Dashboard Design</h3>
    <p><strong>How do I design dashboards?</strong></p>
    <p>Dashboards are designed using a drag-and-drop editor that is intuitive and requires no programming knowledge. This editor is included in every Galyleo Analytics Environment, making it accessible to all users.</p>

    <p><strong>Can I include custom data in my dashboards?</strong></p>
    <p>Yes, you can include data from the Data Plane or upload your own data to be visualized in your dashboards. The platform supports various data formats for maximum flexibility.</p>

    <h3>Publishing and Hosting</h3>
    <p><strong>How do I publish a dashboard?</strong></p>
    <p>Publishing a dashboard is as simple as a single click. The resulting HTML/JavaScript page can be hosted on any web server or shared directly with others.</p>

    <p><strong>What security features are in place for published dashboards?</strong></p>
    <p>Since dashboards are standard HTML/JavaScript pages, they adhere to all standard web security mechanisms, including HTTPS, firewalls, and user authentication as managed by the hosting environment.</p>

    <h3>Future Development</h3>
    <p><strong>What features are planned for the Galyleo Visualization Platform?</strong></p>
    <p>Upcoming features include:
        <ul>
            <li>Support for additional open-source charting and mapping libraries</li>
            <li>Enhanced collaboration tools for team-based dashboard design</li>
            <li>Advanced data transformation and filtering options within the editor</li>
        </ul>
    </p>

    <p><strong>Will there be support for advanced interactivity in dashboards?</strong></p>
    <p>Yes, future updates will enable more interactive features, such as dynamic filtering, linked charts, and real-time data updates, to make dashboards even more engaging and informative.</p>
</body>
</html>
